Schematic highlighting the MoO2 deposition process upon monolayer CVD graphene sheets, where MoO2 nucleation starts upon the graphene edge plane like- sites/defects. Note that longer deposition times result in the MoO2 growing from the edge plane like- sites/defects over onto the basal plane sites until there is a complete insulating layer covering the entire monolayer graphene sheet, resulting in substantially reduced electrochemical activity. Note, sizes are not to scale.

