MoO2 nanowire arrays have been electrodeposited onto the edge plane like- sites/defects of CVD grown monolayer graphene using a polymer-free transfer method, which have been confirmed via physicochemical characterisation. The electrochemical activity pre and post MoO2 electrochemical deposition has been assessed using a near-ideal redox probe and in the latter case indicates that the HET kinetics (kobs0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
